{"id":20096,"date":"2014-12-16T14:07:26","date_gmt":"2014-12-16T10:07:26","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=20096"},"modified":"2019-05-20T15:12:35","modified_gmt":"2019-05-20T11:12:35","slug":"khamr-pour-out-madinah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/12\/16\/khamr-pour-out-madinah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Khamr: Muslims abandon alcohol when the verse comes"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was addressing people in Medina, saying, \u201c<strong>O people, Allah Almighty is alluding to wine. Perhaps Allah will soon reveal an order regarding it. Whoever has some of it, let him sell it and benefit from it<\/strong>.\u201d We did not wait but a little while until the Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, Allah Almighty has forbidden wine. Whoever knows this verse and has some of it, let him neither drink it nor sell it<\/strong>.\u201d The people came out into the street with what they had and poured it out.<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1578<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0633\u064e\u0639\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u062f\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u064a\u064e\u062e\u0652\u0637\u064f\u0628\u064f \u0628\u0650\u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u062f\u0650\u064a\u0646\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e <strong>\u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064f\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\